            "id": "f90d5470a013485492669",
            "questionText": "At a chemical processing plant, a heavy solvent has a density of $!$1.25\\ \\text{g/cm}^3$!$ and a mass of $!$250\\ \\text{kg}$!$. First, convert the density of the heavy solvent to SI units ($!$kg/m^3$!$). Then, calculate the volume of the heavy solvent in cubic meters ($!$m^3$!$).",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "e2229bf16e004f83a5ecd",
                    "stepText": "Let's begin by identifying the correct conversion formula to change density from $!$\\text{g/cm}^3$!$ to $!$\\text{kg/m}^3$!$. Which formula correctly applies the conversion factor?",
